pqueue.priorityqueues

Class LinearPriorityQueue<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • pqueue.priorityqueues.LinearPriorityQueue<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type held by the container.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, PriorityQueue<T>

    public class LinearPriorityQueue<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements PriorityQueue<T>

    LinearPriorityQueue is a PriorityQueue implemented as a linear Collection of common FIFOQueues, where the FIFOQueues themselves hold objects with the same priority (in the order they were inserted).

    You must implement the methods in this file! To receive any credit for the unit tests related to this class, your implementation must use whichever linear Collection you want (e.g ArrayList, LinkedList, Queue), or even the various List and FIFOQueue implementations that we provide for you. You can also use raw arrays, but take a look at GenericArrays if you intend to do so. Note that, unlike ArrayMinHeap, we do not insist that you use a contiguous storage Collection, but any one available (including LinkedList)
